Question: Create two arrays of reg type capable of storing 15 elements. Use $urandom function to add 15 values to the array. Print the value of all the elements of the array on a single line.

/ Create two arrays of reg type capable of storing 15 elements

  reg [7:0] arr1 [0:14];

  reg [7:0] arr2 [0:14];



  initial begin

    // Fill both arrays with random values using $urandom

    for (int i = 0; i < 15; i++) begin

      arr1[i] = $urandom;

      arr2[i] = $urandom;

    end



    // Print the values of arr1 on a single line

    $write("Array 1 values: ");

    for (int i = 0; i < 15; i++) begin

      $write("%0d ", arr1[i]);

    end

    $display(""); // move to next line



    // Print the values of arr2 on a single line

    $write("Array 2 values: ");

    for (int i = 0; i < 15; i++) begin

      $write("%0d ", arr2[i]);

    end

    $display(""); // move to next line



    $finish;

  end



endmodule
